    <briefdescription>
<para>This <computeroutput><ref refid="classAdaptableUnaryFunction" kindref="compound" external="/home/runner/work/cgal-cn/cgal-cn/build_doc/doc_tags/Manual.tag">AdaptableUnaryFunction</ref></computeroutput> computes the total degree of a <computeroutput><ref refid="classPolynomialTraits__d_1a4526aab58b9438fcad4cdfc26f7f1cf6" kindref="member">PolynomialTraits_d::Polynomial_d</ref></computeroutput>. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para></para>
<para>Given a (multivariate) monomial the sum of all appearing exponents is the total degree of this monomial. The total degree of a polynomial <formula id="21">$ p$</formula> is the maximum of the total degrees of all appearing (multivariate) monomials in <formula id="21">$ p$</formula>.</para>
<para>For instance the total degree of <formula id="36">$ p = x_0^2x_1^3+x_1^4$</formula> is <formula id="147">$ 5$</formula>.</para>
<para>The total degree of the zero polynomial is set to <formula id="39">$ 0$</formula>. From the mathematical point of view this should be <formula id="148">$ -\infty$</formula>, but this would imply an inconvenient return type.</para>
